      • isConvertable

        public boolean isConvertable(int[][] key1,
                             int[][] key2)
        Determines whether key1 can be converted into key2
        Parameters:
        key1 - first key
        key2 - second key
        Returns:
        whether key1 can be converted into key2
        Precondition:
        key1 != null && key2 != null && isKey(key2) && isKey(key2)
        Modifies:
        None
        Postcondition:
        \result == (\forall r; key1.has(r); CR(key1[r], key2[r])),
        where CR(row1, row2) = row1.length == row2.length && (\forall i; row1.has(i); row1[i] <= row2[i])
